<p>To remove the negative exponent, multiply both sides of the equation by $e^x$,</p>

\[\begin{align*}
	e^x-6e^{-x} &amp;= -1 \\
	e^x (e^x-6e^{-x}) &amp;= e^x(-1) \\
	e^{2x}-6 &amp;= -e^x \\
	e^{2x}+e^x-6 &amp;= 0
\end{align*}\]

<p>The factor the equation,</p>

\[\begin{align*}
	(e^x+3)(e^x-2) &amp;= 0
\end{align*}\]

<p>Thus,</p>

\[\begin{align*}
	x+3 &amp;= 0    &amp;   x-2 &amp;= 0 \\
	x &amp;= -3 &amp;   x &amp;= 2      \tagans
\end{align*}\]

